span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushadextinkerdink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadex Tinkerdink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 1:23:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1022.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: horses and prices and...stuff</span><hr size=1> Ide say dont buy the horse if you *ever* intend to sell it back.  You lose a lot of cash (the price npcs offer for the bridle is not what you get when you sell it!).<br>
<br>
Buy gear.  The zheart will only be usefull for the stats really until 56.  Dunno prices on your server, but maybe earing of solstice, boots of flowing slime, and fill out your other slots with decent gear with the remainder of cash (really depends on the boot costs for your server). <p><A HREF="http://shade.austin2600.org"><img src="http://shade.austin2600.org/fishsig1.jpg"> </a><p>
